WEBVTT

00:01.740 --> 00:03.873
FUTURAMA IS BROUGHT
TO YOU BY

00:04.003 --> 00:09.269
ARACHNO SPORES, THE FATAL SPORE WITH THE FUNNY NAME.

00:38.037 --> 00:40.082
[ Announcer ]
Cop Departmentis real.

00:40.213 --> 00:42.171
The people you see
are not actors.

00:42.302 --> 00:44.783
Most of them aren't even people.

00:44.914 --> 00:46.002
Come on, man.

00:46.133 --> 00:47.176
I didn't fire off
no laser.

00:47.307 --> 00:48.917
Then why is there
a smoking hole

00:49.048 --> 00:50.267
in your ceiling, sir?

00:50.398 --> 00:51.573
What?

00:51.703 --> 00:56.055
Crazy upstairs lady
must have been shooting down.

00:56.185 --> 00:59.189
Sir, you're on the top floor
of this particular domicile.

00:59.320 --> 01:02.323
You get that [ Bleep ] camera
out of my house.

01:02.453 --> 01:04.063
Just relax, ma'am.

01:04.194 --> 01:05.804
Sir, sir, put down the lamp.

01:05.935 --> 01:07.153
[ Glass Shattering ]

01:07.284 --> 01:09.286
Okay, okay.
I'm cooperating.

01:09.417 --> 01:12.593
That's it.
Now put up your hands.Nice and slow.

01:12.724 --> 01:13.986
Aw, yeah.

01:14.117 --> 01:16.162
And while you're at it,
un-blur your face.

01:16.293 --> 01:18.164
Oh, man.

01:18.295 --> 01:19.557
[ Leela ]
HEY, BENDER.

01:19.688 --> 01:22.037
I THOUGHT YOU SAID YOU
WERE IN THIS EPISODE.

01:22.168 --> 01:24.170
NAH, THIS WEEK
I'M ON CAUGHT ON TAPE 3

01:24.301 --> 01:26.302
'CAUSE OF WHAT I DID
IN THE COFFEEPOT.

01:27.174 --> 01:29.871
I'm sorry.
I'm really sorry.

01:30.001 --> 01:32.396
I'm just going through
some things.

01:32.527 --> 01:33.876
Ooh!

01:35.746 --> 01:37.183
I'm going in.

01:39.098 --> 01:42.231
[ Announcer ]
Cop Departmentwill return
after these messages.

01:42.362 --> 01:45.843
Is today's hectic lifestyle
making you tense and impatient?

01:45.974 --> 01:47.367
SHUT UP AND GET TO THE POINT!

01:47.497 --> 01:51.763
Then come relive the carefree
days of yore at Past-O-Rama

01:51.894 --> 01:54.114
where old New York comes alive.

01:54.243 --> 01:57.290
It's like stepping back
into the year 2000.

01:57.420 --> 01:59.554
Time for
the mammoth hunt, dudes.

01:59.683 --> 02:00.858
[ Yelling ]

02:00.989 --> 02:04.385
[ Trumpeting ]

02:04.515 --> 02:07.301
Let's disco dance,
Hammurabi.

02:07.430 --> 02:08.866
Dyn-o-mite!

02:08.997 --> 02:10.694
[ Disco Music Playing ]

02:13.263 --> 02:16.484
SOUNDS LIKE YOUR KIND OF
PLACE, FRY. WANT TO GO?NAH.

02:16.614 --> 02:18.615
IF I EVER WANT TO GO BACK
TO THE YEAR 2000

02:18.747 --> 02:20.270
I'LL JUST FREEZE MYSELF AGAIN.

02:20.401 --> 02:23.055
COME ON, FRY.
I REALLY WANNA SEE IT.

02:23.186 --> 02:25.622
YOU KNOW HOW I YEARN
FOR A SIMPLER TIME...

02:25.753 --> 02:28.060
A TIME OF BARN DANCES
AND BUGGY RIDES

02:28.191 --> 02:31.586
BEFORE LIFE WAS CHEAPENED BY
HEARTLESS, HIGH-TECH MACHINES.

02:31.716 --> 02:33.240
BUT, BENDER, YOU AREA--

02:33.370 --> 02:35.372
♪ LA, LA, LA, LA, LA, LA,
LA, LA, LA, LA, LA, LA ♪

02:39.507 --> 02:41.944
COOL. IT'S JUST LIKE
THE GOOD OLD DAYS.

02:42.074 --> 02:45.164
GIVE ME YOUR WALLET
OR I'LL CUT YOU!

02:45.295 --> 02:49.299
LEELA, GET A PICTURE
OF ME BEING "MUGGED."

02:49.430 --> 02:50.865
I'LL TAKE THE
CAMERA, TOO.

02:50.996 --> 02:52.301
[ Fry Laughing ]

02:52.432 --> 02:53.389
[ Clearing Throat ]

02:53.521 --> 02:54.870
LEARNING IS FUN.

02:55.000 --> 02:58.395
OOH, ANCIENT
WALL STREET.

02:58.526 --> 03:00.180
[ Buzzer Sounding ]

03:00.310 --> 03:03.835
[ All Screaming In Anguish ]

03:03.966 --> 03:05.401
[ Multiple Thuds ]

03:05.532 --> 03:07.274
[ Bell Rings ]

03:07.403 --> 03:11.277
[ All Cheering
Enthusiastically ]

03:11.407 --> 03:12.974
I DIRECT YOUR ATTENTION

03:13.104 --> 03:15.194
TO THIS ANCIENT
AND MYSTERIOUS TABLET

03:15.324 --> 03:17.413
WHICH HAS YET TO BE DECIPHERED.

03:17.545 --> 03:18.502
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT IT MEANS?

03:18.633 --> 03:19.937
YEAH, I ASKED A COP ONCE.

03:20.068 --> 03:21.418
IT MEANS, "UP YOURS, KID."

03:21.549 --> 03:22.550
I GOT TO SAY

03:22.680 --> 03:26.205
I'M REALLY ENJOYING THE DAY OUT
WITH YOU PEOPLE.

03:26.336 --> 03:28.295
HEY, HEY! A SUICIDE BOOTH.

03:28.425 --> 03:29.425
SO LONG, SUCKERS.

03:29.556 --> 03:30.775
UH, SORRY, BENDER.

03:30.906 --> 03:32.908
THAT'S JUST
A PHONE BOOTH.OH.

03:33.038 --> 03:34.082
WHAT WERE
THEY USED FOR?

03:34.213 --> 03:36.085
IN NEW YORK?
BATHROOMS.

03:36.216 --> 03:37.347
OH.

03:37.478 --> 03:40.567
I-I'LL BE OUT IN A SEC.

03:43.745 --> 03:46.574
"TOKENS ONLY."
HOW DOES THIS WORK?

03:46.704 --> 03:48.097
I'LL SHOW YOU.

03:48.228 --> 03:51.099
OH, IT'S A TURNSTILE.

03:55.757 --> 03:56.888
WHAT'S THIS?

03:57.019 --> 03:59.586
[ Sniffing ]
ANOTHER BATHROOM?

03:59.716 --> 04:02.459
NO, IT'S A MOBILE
APARTMENT WITH NO RENT.

04:02.590 --> 04:03.286
[ Sighs ]

04:03.417 --> 04:05.331
COME ON, FRY.
GET UP.

04:05.461 --> 04:07.247
AH...

04:12.338 --> 04:13.340
WOW.

04:13.469 --> 04:15.776
THE BURIAL CHAMBER
OF THE 20th CENTURY'S

04:15.907 --> 04:17.343
GREATEST SPIRITUAL LEADER--

04:17.473 --> 04:18.562
AL SHARPTON.

04:18.692 --> 04:19.694
OOH.

04:19.824 --> 04:22.783
NOW, THIS GUY HAD TASTE.

04:22.913 --> 04:26.004
IT SAYS HE WAS MUMMIFIED
IN CEREMONIAL VESTMENTS.

04:26.134 --> 04:28.398
WE SOMETIMES CALLED
IT A JOGGING SUIT.

04:31.444 --> 04:34.795
[ Automated Voice ]
The traffic jams of old New York
were a public forum

04:34.925 --> 04:37.406
for the free interchange
of opinion.

04:37.538 --> 04:38.800
[ Car Horns Blaring ]

04:38.930 --> 04:40.235
MOVE IT,
CRAP-FOR-BRAINS!

04:40.367 --> 04:42.933
BUG OFF!GET HOME, BASTARD MAN!

04:43.064 --> 04:46.286
[ Voice ] It all started with
Gerald Ford's famous invention

04:46.415 --> 04:50.290
the automo-car,
which was powered by
a tank of burning fossils.

04:50.420 --> 04:53.509
Here we see
a 20th-century assembly line

04:53.641 --> 04:57.427
where cars were constructed
by primitive robots.

04:57.557 --> 05:01.865
[ Chanting ]
OOH-GAH, OOH-GAH, OOH-GAH!
OOH-GAH, OOH-GAH, OOH-GAH!

05:01.997 --> 05:05.653
WE'VE COME
A LONGWAY, BABY.

05:05.783 --> 05:08.437
The fruit
of the robots' labor was this--

05:08.569 --> 05:11.788
the stately 1992 LaToura.

05:11.920 --> 05:13.355
HEY, MY GIRLFRIEND
HAD ONE OF THOSE.

05:13.487 --> 05:15.531
ACTUALLY, IT WASN'T HERS.
IT WAS HER DAD'S.

05:15.663 --> 05:17.012
ACTUALLY, SHE WASN'T
MY GIRLFRIEND.

05:17.141 --> 05:19.319
SHE JUST LIVED NEXT DOOR
AND NEVER CLOSED HER CURTAINS.

05:19.449 --> 05:21.798
FRY, REMEMBER WHEN
I TOLD YOU

05:21.930 --> 05:23.887
ABOUT ALWAYS ENDING YOUR STORIES
A SENTENCE EARLIER?

05:24.019 --> 05:26.064
COME ON, LET'S SNEAK
IN FOR A CLOSER LOOK.

05:28.893 --> 05:31.766
SIR, WE DON'T TOUCH
THE ANTIQUES, SIR.

05:31.896 --> 05:34.985
YOU DON'T-- UH,
I'M SORRY, YOU WORK HERE.

05:35.117 --> 05:37.901
I SHOULD HAVE REALIZED FROM THAT
RIDICULOUS GETUP YOU'RE WEARING.

05:38.033 --> 05:40.382
HEY, THIS IS
FROM MILLER'S OUTPOS--

05:40.514 --> 05:43.343
I MEAN, YEAH,
I-I WORK HERE ALL RIGHT.

05:43.473 --> 05:45.562
HERE.
MOVE THIS RUST BUCKET

05:45.692 --> 05:47.521
OUT BEHIND
ST. KOCH'S CATHEDRAL.

05:47.651 --> 05:49.086
[ Snorts And Laughs ]

05:50.915 --> 05:53.569
DID YOU DRIVE MUCH
IN THE 20th CENTURY, FRY?

05:53.701 --> 05:56.225
NO. NO ONE IN
NEW YORK DROVE.

05:56.355 --> 05:57.574
THERE WAS TOO
MUCH TRAFFIC.

05:57.704 --> 05:58.706
[ Grinding ]

05:58.836 --> 06:01.795
NICE. LISTEN TO
THAT BABY PURR.

06:01.925 --> 06:03.406
THERE'S A BABY IN THERE, HUH?

06:03.536 --> 06:05.495
[ Engine Revving ]

06:10.630 --> 06:14.156
IT'S JUST LIKE RIDING
A BICYCLE-- AY-YI-YI!

06:14.286 --> 06:16.245
[ All Screaming ]

06:18.247 --> 06:21.468
[ Orchestra Playing
"New York, New York" ]

06:23.470 --> 06:25.254
[ Screaming Continues ]

06:25.384 --> 06:27.387
[ Tires Squealing ]

06:27.516 --> 06:30.259
[ Screaming Continues ]

06:30.389 --> 06:31.391
[ Loud Crash ]

06:31.521 --> 06:34.524
OH, I THINK
I GOT WHIPLASH.

06:34.654 --> 06:37.134
YOU CAN'T HAVE WHIPLASH.
YOU DON'T HAVE A NECK.

06:37.266 --> 06:39.485
I MEANT ASS WHIPLASH.

06:39.615 --> 06:42.619
I'M JUST GLAD WE HIT SOMETHING.
I THOUGHT WE'D NEVER STOP.

06:44.055 --> 06:45.492
[ All Gasping ]

06:45.622 --> 06:47.057
[ Groans ]

06:47.189 --> 06:48.711
I THINK I GOT WHIPLASH.

06:48.843 --> 06:50.540
[ Groans ]

07:04.293 --> 07:07.338
HOW'S THAT ROBOT
I RAN OVER?

07:07.470 --> 07:09.516
WE DID ALL WE COULD.

07:09.646 --> 07:10.516
[ Gasps ]
YOU MEAN HE'S--

07:10.646 --> 07:13.127
GOOD AS NEW? YES.

07:13.257 --> 07:17.524
LEELA, ZOIDBERG, THE REST
OF YOU, THIS IS FLEXO.

07:17.653 --> 07:18.959
SWEET LLAMAS
OF THE BAHAMAS!

07:19.089 --> 07:20.613
EXCEPT FOR THAT
STYLISH BEARD

07:20.744 --> 07:22.485
HE LOOK JUST
LIKE BENDER.

07:22.615 --> 07:23.704
NO DUH, DREADLOCK.

07:23.834 --> 07:25.444
WE'RE BOTH
BENDING UNITS.

07:25.574 --> 07:27.663
HEY, BRO-BOT, WHAT'S
YOUR SERIAL NUMBER?

07:27.795 --> 07:29.579
3370318.

07:29.709 --> 07:32.930
NO WAY.
MINE'S 2716057.

07:33.060 --> 07:35.367
[ Hearty Laughter ]

07:35.497 --> 07:37.586
[ Laughing ]
I DON'T GET IT.

07:37.718 --> 07:41.112
WE'RE BOTH EXPRESSIBLE
AS THE SUM OF TWO CUBES.WHOO!

07:41.939 --> 07:42.983
SO, UH, FLEXO...

07:43.113 --> 07:45.595
SORRY ABOUT CRUSHING
YOUR BODY LIKE THAT.

07:45.725 --> 07:46.509
YOU OKAY NOW?

07:46.639 --> 07:49.033
WELL, I DON'T FEEL
AS BAD AS YOU LOOK.

07:49.163 --> 07:51.382
[ Laughs ]

07:51.514 --> 07:53.168
AH, I'M JUST
MESSING WITH
YOU, KID.

07:53.298 --> 07:54.386
YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.

07:54.516 --> 07:55.822
THAT'S SOME FACE
YOU GOT, THOUGH.

07:55.952 --> 07:57.651
I THINK THEY GOT
A CREAM FOR THAT.

07:57.781 --> 07:59.391
[ Laughs ]

07:59.521 --> 08:01.567
NO, YOU'RE GREAT.WELL, JUST LET ME KNOW...

08:01.697 --> 08:04.048
IF THERE'S
ANYTHING I CAN DO
TO MAKE IT UP TO YOU.

08:04.178 --> 08:06.790
ACTUALLY, YOUR LITTLE STUNT
DID A NUMBER ON MY BACK.

08:06.920 --> 08:10.401
YOU MIND RUBBING
IT FOR ME?UH, SURE.

08:10.533 --> 08:12.579
AW, YEAH, THAT'S IT.
LITTLE LOWER.

08:12.709 --> 08:13.709
HOW'S THAT?LOWER.

08:13.841 --> 08:16.582
YEAH, THAT'S GETTING IT.
LITTLE LOWER, THOUGH.

08:16.713 --> 08:18.454
I CAN'T GET
ANY LOWER THAN THIS.

08:18.584 --> 08:21.935
I'LL SAY. YOU'RE
RUBBING MY ASS.
[ Laughs ]

08:22.065 --> 08:24.939
[ Both Guffaw ]

08:28.682 --> 08:30.074
HEY, UH, CHECK IT OUT HERE.

08:30.204 --> 08:31.598
SIX BEAUTIFUL DEVICES.

08:31.728 --> 08:33.817
THEY KNOW WHAT YOU LIKE
AND THEY'LL DO IT

08:33.947 --> 08:36.254
TO WITHIN A TOLERANCE
OF ONE MICRON.

08:36.384 --> 08:38.605
[ Whistles And Catcalls ]

08:38.735 --> 08:40.823
SPIN THOSE
FANS, BABY!

08:40.955 --> 08:42.739
ALL RIGHT, MAMA!

08:43.610 --> 08:44.524
SPIN IT, BABY.

08:44.653 --> 08:46.525
[ Whistles And Catcalls ]

08:51.442 --> 08:52.575
I DON'T LIKE THIS PLACE.

08:52.706 --> 08:55.534
IT'S 120 DEGREES
AND THERE'S VERY LITTLE OXYGEN.

08:55.664 --> 08:57.711
SHUT UP AND HOOT.

08:57.841 --> 08:59.277
[ Drums Crescendo ]

09:00.844 --> 09:04.543
[ Whistles And Catcalls ]

09:08.677 --> 09:10.679
HUBBA, HUBBA.
SHE IS BUILT--

09:10.811 --> 09:12.639
IN MEXICO,
I BELIEVE.

09:12.769 --> 09:14.553
AND THAT AIN'T SILICON.

09:14.683 --> 09:17.120
IT'S TUNGSTEN,
AND PLENTY OF IT.

09:17.251 --> 09:19.775
UH, YEAH.
LOOK AT THAT EXHAUST FAN.

09:19.907 --> 09:20.821
[ Disgusted Snorts ]

09:20.951 --> 09:21.908
PERVERT.

09:22.038 --> 09:24.346
YOO-HOO!

09:24.475 --> 09:25.782
[ Chuckling ]

09:25.913 --> 09:28.306
OH.

09:28.437 --> 09:29.917
THANKS, MODERATE SPENDER.

09:30.047 --> 09:32.484
PLEASE SELECT
EROTIC TRANSACTION.

09:32.615 --> 09:35.705
YEAH. HOW ABOUT A LAP DANCE
FOR MY PAL HERE?

09:35.836 --> 09:39.709
OOH, YEAH. CHUCK-A-CHONG.

09:39.840 --> 09:42.320
UH, NO, NO, THAT'S
ALL RIGHT, REALLY.

09:42.451 --> 09:44.539
I-- OW! OW! OW! OW! OW!

09:46.673 --> 09:47.890
I'M TELLING YOU.

09:48.022 --> 09:51.111
THERE'S SOMETHING
ABOUT FLEXO I DON'T LIKE.

09:51.241 --> 09:53.114
HEY, FRY, THINK FAST.

09:55.332 --> 09:56.725
GET IT? IT'S CHLORINE.

09:56.856 --> 09:58.553
[ Both Laughing ]

10:00.076 --> 10:01.296
[ Laughing ]

10:01.426 --> 10:03.864
IT'S FUNNY
BECAUSE IT'S POISONOUS.

10:03.994 --> 10:06.649
YEAH, KEEP LAUGHING,
BRINE SHRIMP,
BUT HE'S BAD NEWS.

10:06.779 --> 10:08.346
I REGRET EVER
RUNNING HIM OVER.

10:08.476 --> 10:09.913
TAKE A RAGE DUMP, MON.

10:10.043 --> 10:11.610
HE'S NO WORSE THAN BENDER.

10:11.740 --> 10:13.830
HE'S MUCH WORSE.
HE DRINKS AND SMOKES

10:13.961 --> 10:16.615
AND HE POSTS NAKED PICTURES
OF ME ON THE INTERNET.

10:16.745 --> 10:18.748
THAT'S BENDER
ALL RIGHT.I'M TALKING ABOUT FLEXO.

10:18.879 --> 10:21.794
OH, I GET IT.
THIS IS CUTE.

10:21.924 --> 10:23.884
YOU'RE JEALOUS
OF BENDER'S NEW FRIEND.

10:24.014 --> 10:24.884
NO, I'M NOT.

10:25.014 --> 10:27.975
MARK MY WORDS.
FLEXO'S EVIL.

10:28.105 --> 10:30.542
HE'S THE EVIL BENDER.

10:30.673 --> 10:32.109
RAGE DUMP.

10:33.153 --> 10:34.590
Good news, everyone.

10:34.721 --> 10:38.115
Report to my bedroom
for a private exhibition.

10:38.245 --> 10:39.769
[ All ]
HMM.

10:39.899 --> 10:41.815
EVERYONE GET
IN BED WITH ME.

10:41.945 --> 10:44.513
I HAVE SOMETHING TO SHOW YOU.

10:47.602 --> 10:51.128
FEAST YOUR EYES ON THIS!

10:51.259 --> 10:52.433
[ All Gasping ]

10:52.563 --> 10:54.217
[ Leela ]
IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

10:54.349 --> 10:57.004
[ Amy ] AND HUGE.[ Fry ]
CAN I TOUCH IT?

10:57.134 --> 10:58.658
SO WHAT IS IT ALREADY?

10:58.788 --> 11:01.529
IT'S A SINGLE
ATOM OF JUMBONIUM.

11:01.660 --> 11:02.662
AN ELEMENT SO RARE,

11:02.792 --> 11:06.447
THE NUCLEUS ALONE IS WORTH
MORE THAN $50,000.

11:06.577 --> 11:08.754
- HOW MUCH MORE?
- 100,000.

11:08.884 --> 11:11.452
THAT'S WHY I HID IT HERE,
UNDER MY MATTRESS.

11:11.582 --> 11:14.325
UH, PROFESSOR, CAN WE
DISCUSS THIS SOMEWHERE ELSE?

11:14.456 --> 11:15.804
WHY, CERTAINLY.

11:15.936 --> 11:19.548
THE ATOM SITS ATOP
THIS DIME-STORE TIARA

11:19.678 --> 11:21.201
WHICH WILL BE AWARDED
TO THE WINNER

11:21.331 --> 11:23.116
OF THIS YEAR'S
MISS UNIVERSE PAGEANT

11:23.246 --> 11:25.119
ON THE PLANET TOVA NINE.

11:25.249 --> 11:28.687
YOUR JOB IS TO DELIVER IT
SAFE AND SOUND.

11:28.817 --> 11:31.254
WOW. WHEN I WAS
A LITTLE GIRL ON MARS

11:31.385 --> 11:33.126
I DREAMED OF BEING
MISS UNIVERSE.

11:33.256 --> 11:35.695
THAT'S KIND OF PATHETIC.OH, COME ON, LEELA.

11:35.825 --> 11:38.000
DEEP DOWN, ALL GIRLS
WANT TO BE MISS UNIVERSE.

11:38.131 --> 11:42.004
NOT ME.REALLY? MAYBE IT'S JUST
CUTE GIRLS.

11:42.135 --> 11:44.485
DUE TO THE ATOM'S
TREMENDOUS VALUE

11:44.615 --> 11:47.489
PLANET EXPRESS WOULD GO BANKRUPT
IF IT WERE STOLEN.

11:47.619 --> 11:51.667
THEREFORE, WE'LL NEED TO HIRE ON
ADDITIONAL SECURITY
FOR THE MISSION.

11:51.798 --> 11:54.844
OH, OH, OH!
OH, MR. PROFESSOR?
RIGHT HERE!

11:54.975 --> 11:57.455
MAYBE WE SHOULD STICK WITH
PEOPLE WE KNOW AND TRUST.

11:57.586 --> 11:58.934
I MEAN, FLEXO'S GREAT, BUT--

11:59.066 --> 12:00.197
FLEXO'S GREAT, YOU SAY?

12:00.327 --> 12:02.285
OH, WELL,
THAT'S GOOD ENOUGH FOR ME.

12:02.417 --> 12:04.724
WELCOME ABOARD, LAD.

12:04.854 --> 12:07.856
[ Evil Laughter ]

12:14.515 --> 12:17.083
SPACE BANDITOS HAVE BEEN
OPERATING IN THIS QUADRANT

12:17.213 --> 12:19.869
SO YOU'LL EACH TAKE
EIGHT-HOUR SHIFTS
GUARDING THE SAFE.

12:20.000 --> 12:22.697
FIRST BENDER,
THEN FLEXO, THEN FRY.

12:22.828 --> 12:24.918
WAIT, HOLD ON.
I DON'T LIKE
THE SOUND OF THAT.

12:25.048 --> 12:26.658
LET'S JUST GO
ALPHABETICALLY.

12:26.788 --> 12:29.749
OKAY. FIRST BENDER,
THEN FLEXO, THEN FRY.

12:29.879 --> 12:31.620
WAIT, LET'S GO BY RANK.

12:31.750 --> 12:34.927
OKAY. FIRST BENDER,
THEN FLEXO, THEN FRY.

12:35.057 --> 12:36.494
FLEXO OUTRANKS ME?

12:36.625 --> 12:39.409
THAT'S "FLEXO
OUTRANKS ME, SIR."

12:44.240 --> 12:46.287
HALT! WHO GOES THERE?DON'T POINT THAT AT ME.

12:46.417 --> 12:47.418
FRY WHO?

12:47.548 --> 12:49.289
LOOK, I KNOW
FLEXO'S YOUR FRIEND,

12:49.419 --> 12:51.682
BUT I DON'T TRUST HIM
ALONE WITH THE ATOM.

12:51.813 --> 12:53.076
MY GOD, FRY.

12:53.206 --> 12:55.948
JUST 'CAUSE THE GUY'S GOT
A BEARD, YOU LABEL HIM AS EVIL?

12:56.078 --> 12:57.732
WELL, I GOT A LABEL
FOR YOU, PAL--

12:57.864 --> 13:00.039
AN UGLY LITTLE WORD
CALLED "PREJUDICE."

13:00.214 --> 13:01.475
I'M NOT PREJUDICED.

13:01.605 --> 13:03.870
AW, SAVE IT FOR THE
CROSS BURNING, ADOLF.

13:08.482 --> 13:11.051
KEEPING AN EYE
ON THE SAFE?YOU KNOW IT.

13:12.442 --> 13:14.096
WELL, LOOKS LIKE
IT'S MY SHIFT.

13:14.227 --> 13:16.883
YOU LIE DOWN AND GO
OFF-LINE FOR A WHILE.

13:17.013 --> 13:18.014
[ Yawning ]

13:18.144 --> 13:19.668
ALL RIGHT.

13:23.715 --> 13:26.500
[ Whistling Jaunty Tune ]

13:26.630 --> 13:28.371
[ Evil Chuckling ]

13:28.503 --> 13:29.591
CAUGHT YOU!

13:29.721 --> 13:31.461
I SAW YOU LOOKING
AT THE ATOM.

13:31.592 --> 13:33.725
SO? I LOOK AT
LOTS OF ATOMS.

13:33.855 --> 13:36.032
SHOULDN'T YOU BE RESTING UP
FOR YOUR SHIFT?

13:36.163 --> 13:38.774
OH, YOU'D LIKE IT IF I WENT
TO SLEEP, WOULDN'T YOU?

13:38.904 --> 13:40.863
WHATEVER IT TAKES
TO SHUT YOUR YAPPER.

13:40.994 --> 13:42.125
[ Laughing ]

13:42.255 --> 13:44.039
NO, I'M JUST KIDDING.
YOU'RE A JOKER.

13:44.171 --> 13:45.562
YEAH? WELL, HERE'S
A FUNNY JOKE--

13:45.693 --> 13:48.000
I'M GOING TO SIT
RIGHT HERE TILL
IT'S MY SHIFT.

13:48.130 --> 13:50.698
- SUIT YOURSELF, SKINBAG.
- THAT I WILL.

13:50.830 --> 13:51.918
- GOOD.
- GOOD.

13:52.048 --> 13:52.875
- GOOD.
- GOOD.

13:53.005 --> 13:54.136
- GOOD.
- GOOD.

13:55.269 --> 13:56.923
GOOD.

13:59.142 --> 14:00.708
[ Watch Beeps ]

14:00.840 --> 14:02.014
WELL, THAT'S EIGHT HOURS.

14:02.144 --> 14:04.408
YEAH, EIGHT HOURS
OF SOLID BOREDOM.

14:04.538 --> 14:06.322
NAH, I'M KIDDING.

14:06.453 --> 14:07.759
YOU'RE A WONDERFUL MAN.

14:09.630 --> 14:12.721
FINALLY, THE ATOM IS SAFE.

14:12.851 --> 14:14.070
[ Snoring ]

14:26.735 --> 14:28.868
HUH?
[ Yawning ]

14:28.998 --> 14:30.303
[ Screaming ]

14:31.957 --> 14:35.091
WHAT IS IT?
[ Gasping ]
MY GOD!

14:35.221 --> 14:37.005
- DID YOU HEAR MARACAS?
- NO.

14:37.136 --> 14:38.572
THEN IT WASN'T SPACE BANDITOS.

14:38.702 --> 14:40.009
BENDER, LOCK DOWN THE SHIP.

14:40.139 --> 14:41.663
DON'T LET FLEXO
ESCAPE.

14:41.793 --> 14:43.011
AYE, AYE, CAPTAIN.

14:43.143 --> 14:46.101
IT APPEARS THAT FLEXO
HAS OUTWITTED US ALL...

14:46.232 --> 14:50.192
ESPECIALLY ME-- BENDER.

14:54.240 --> 14:56.330
HOW COULD FLEXO HAVE
STOLEN THE ATOM?

14:56.460 --> 14:58.114
HE MUST HAVE USED
A SLEEP RAY ON ME.

14:58.245 --> 14:59.899
SLEEP RAYS EXIST
IN THE FUTURE, RIGHT?

15:00.028 --> 15:02.162
- NO.
- MMM. THEN I MUST
HAVE FALLEN ASLEEP.

15:02.292 --> 15:04.903
WELL, YOU WERE SURE RIGHT
ABOUT FLEXO BEING EVIL.

15:05.033 --> 15:08.124
I LOCKED DOWN THE EXITS,
BUT HE MAY HAVE
ALREADY GOTTEN AWAY.

15:08.254 --> 15:10.996
OKAY, THANKS, BENDER.
LET'S FAN OUT AND LOOK
FOR HIM.

15:11.126 --> 15:14.000
ROGER THAT. I GOT A MAP
OF THE SHIP RIGHT HERE.

15:14.129 --> 15:15.653
KEEP AN EYE
ON FRY.

15:15.783 --> 15:18.874
WE CAN'T RULE OUT
THE POSSIBILITY
THAT HE DID IT.

15:24.096 --> 15:25.272
AHA!

15:28.057 --> 15:29.580
AHA!

15:29.711 --> 15:32.278
UH, SEARCHING. HMM.

15:32.408 --> 15:35.020
FRY, WHY ARE YOU
LOOKING FOR FLEXO

15:35.150 --> 15:36.673
IN MY UNDERPANTS
DRAWER?

15:36.804 --> 15:38.284
I DIDN'T FIND HIM HERE
TEN MINUTES AGO

15:38.414 --> 15:40.025
SO I THOUGHT IT WAS TIME
TO CHECK AGAIN.

15:40.155 --> 15:42.028
OW!

15:42.158 --> 15:45.118
WELL, HE WASN'T
IN THE, UH,
KITCHEN ROOM.

15:45.248 --> 15:48.730
SAY, BENDER, CAN I HOLD
THAT MAP FOR A SECOND?

15:48.860 --> 15:52.168
AND LEAVE ME HIGH AND DRY
IN CASE OF A SCAVENGER HUNT?

15:52.298 --> 15:53.212
I THINK NOT.

15:53.342 --> 15:54.735
GIVE IT UP!

15:54.865 --> 15:55.998
[ Both Grunting ]

15:57.652 --> 16:00.307
ALL RIGHT! TAKE IT.
SHEESH.

16:04.658 --> 16:07.443
WELL, LOOKS LIKE FLEXO
GOT AWAY CLEAN.

16:07.575 --> 16:09.054
IT'S A DARN SHAME.

16:09.184 --> 16:12.231
HE MUST HAVE JUMPED SHIP
WITH THE ATOM
THE SECOND WE LANDED.

16:12.361 --> 16:16.452
OR MAYBE...
HE NEVER LEFT AT ALL!

16:16.583 --> 16:18.325
WAIT A MINUTE.
YOU'RE BENDER.

16:18.455 --> 16:20.066
OF COURSE. WHO SAID I WASN'T?

16:20.196 --> 16:23.155
BUT WHY WERE YOU WEARING
THAT SCARF AND THE TURTLENECK

16:23.286 --> 16:24.461
AND THIS FRUITY NUMBER?

16:24.591 --> 16:26.549
IT'S A LITTLE THING
CALLED STYLE.

16:26.681 --> 16:29.030
LOOK IT UP SOMETIME.

16:34.514 --> 16:36.995
[ Evil Chuckling ]

16:37.125 --> 16:39.128
[ Panting ]

16:42.304 --> 16:45.961
OUR NINTH FINALIST,
MISS METHANE PLANET--

16:46.091 --> 16:48.442
HALATINA SMOGMEYER.

16:48.572 --> 16:50.269
[ Cheering And Applause ]

16:50.399 --> 16:54.187
[ Gasping And Choking ]

16:54.317 --> 16:56.754
AND OUR TENTH
AND FINAL FINALIST

16:56.884 --> 17:00.758
MISS EARTH'S MOON--
THE CRUSHINATOR.

17:03.239 --> 17:05.111
[ Man's Voice ]
THANK YOU, BOB BARKER.

17:05.240 --> 17:09.115
I'M AS HAPPY AS A GIRL CAN BE.
END STATEMENT.

17:09.244 --> 17:11.900
WHICH ONE
OF THESE LOVELY WOMANOIDS

17:12.030 --> 17:14.903
WILL TAKE HOME
THE ATOMIC TIARA?

17:15.034 --> 17:16.773
DOWNPLAY THE TIARA.

17:16.904 --> 17:18.515
UH, WE'LL FIND OUT

17:18.645 --> 17:21.736
AFTER THESE
SUBLIMINAL MESSAGES.

17:24.130 --> 17:26.174
SO YOU LOST THE ATOM, HUH?

17:26.306 --> 17:28.481
YOU'RE GARBAGE, HUMAN GARBAGE!

17:28.612 --> 17:31.049
DO YOU BRAIN-DEAD
SPACE JOCKEYS
HAVE ANY IDEA

17:31.180 --> 17:32.963
HOW MUCH THAT
THING IS WORTH?

17:33.095 --> 17:35.141
- 100,000?
- 200,000?

17:35.270 --> 17:36.403
200,001?

17:36.532 --> 17:38.491
YOU'RE CLOSEST
WITHOUT GOING OVER.

17:38.622 --> 17:40.189
WELL, UH,
WE'LL BE LEAVING NOW.

17:40.319 --> 17:42.409
IF YOU COULD JUST SIGN
THIS FORM SAYING
YOU RECEIVED THE ATOM.

17:42.538 --> 17:44.063
I'M NOT SIGNING SQUAT.

17:44.192 --> 17:47.066
YOU FIND ME THAT DAMN TIARA
BEFORE THE PAGEANT ENDS.

17:47.195 --> 17:49.285
BUT, MR. BARKER--ENOUGH OUT OF YOU!

17:49.415 --> 17:50.852
I MAY BE AGAINST
THE FUR INDUSTRY

17:50.981 --> 17:53.984
BUT THAT WON'T STOP ME
FROM SKINNING YOU ALIVE...

17:54.115 --> 17:56.204
AS LONG AS NO ONE WEARS
THE SKIN.

17:56.336 --> 17:58.294
[ Wheels Squeaking ]

17:58.424 --> 18:01.515
WELL, GENTLEMEN,
IT APPEARS WE'RE BONED.

18:02.558 --> 18:04.083
HEY!FLEXO!

18:04.212 --> 18:05.084
[ Leela ]
GET HIM!

18:05.213 --> 18:07.825
[ Playing Fanfare ]

18:10.175 --> 18:12.178
[ Applause ]

18:15.181 --> 18:16.964
[ Jingling ]

18:17.096 --> 18:21.143
NEXT UP, IN WHAT IS GENEROUSLY
CALLED "THE TALENT COMPETITION"

18:21.273 --> 18:25.799
PERFORMING A TRADITIONAL
GANGSTER RAP, MISS-- WHAT THE--

18:25.930 --> 18:27.148
[ Screaming ]

18:28.628 --> 18:30.631
GOT YA!

18:32.198 --> 18:34.808
FIGHT! FIGHT! FIGHT!
FIGHT! FIGHT!

18:34.939 --> 18:37.246
SHOOT HIM!
HE'S CHOKING ME!

18:37.376 --> 18:39.814
NO, SHOOT HIM!
HE'S CHOKING ME!

18:41.816 --> 18:43.686
I DON'T KNOW WHICH ONE TO SHOOT.

18:43.817 --> 18:46.125
FLEXO! SHOOT FLEXO.

18:48.778 --> 18:50.346
[ All Screaming ]

18:53.393 --> 18:55.134
[ Man's Voice ]
WOMEN ONLY ROOM!

18:55.263 --> 18:57.005
[ Imitating Drum Machine ]

19:04.446 --> 19:07.189
ALL RIGHT, ENOUGH OF THIS.

19:10.323 --> 19:12.106
[ Both Groaning ]

19:15.284 --> 19:18.505
[ All Gasping ]

19:18.634 --> 19:20.070
THERE'S THE ATOM!

19:21.289 --> 19:22.596
AW, GEEZ.

19:22.726 --> 19:24.858
BENDER?
YOUSTOLE THE ATOM?

19:24.989 --> 19:28.166
YEAH, BUT I CAN EXPLAIN.
IT'S VERY VALUABLE.

19:28.297 --> 19:31.038
I SAW HIM SNATCH IT
WHILE FRY WAS ASLEEP.

19:31.170 --> 19:33.388
THAT'S WHY I RAN
TO TELL BOB BARKER.

19:33.519 --> 19:35.130
WHOA, WHOA,
WAIT A SECOND.

19:35.260 --> 19:37.262
YOU MEAN BENDER
IS THE EVIL BENDER?

19:37.393 --> 19:39.265
I AM SHOCKED, SHOCKED!

19:39.394 --> 19:40.614
WELL, NOT THAT SHOCKED.

19:40.743 --> 19:43.050
I'M SORRY
WE SUSPECTED YOU, FLEXO.

19:43.182 --> 19:45.183
IT'S JUST, WHAT
WITH THE BEARD AND ALL--

19:45.314 --> 19:48.056
DON'T EVEN BOTHER.
YOU PEOPLE SICKEN ME.

19:48.186 --> 19:51.885
I PUT MY LIFE ON THE LINE
TO GUARD THAT ATOM AND THIS
IS HOW YOU REPAY ME?

19:52.016 --> 19:55.280
WELL, YOU CAN GO ROT
FOR ALL I CARE.

19:55.411 --> 19:56.630
[ Laughing ]

19:56.759 --> 19:59.285
NAH, I'M JUST KIDDING.
YOU GUYS ARE ALL RIGHT.

19:59.414 --> 20:01.200
[ Laughing ]

20:01.329 --> 20:03.332
I'M SO CONFUSED.

20:03.462 --> 20:05.290
THE BENDER I LIKED
TURNED OUT TO BE EVIL

20:05.421 --> 20:07.770
AND THE BENDER
I HATED WAS GOOD.

20:07.902 --> 20:11.471
HOW CAN I LIVE MY LIFE
WHEN I CAN'T TELL GOOD
FROM EVIL?

20:11.601 --> 20:15.431
AH, THEY'RE BOTH
FINE CHOICES--
WHATEVER FLOATS YOUR BOAT.

20:17.564 --> 20:20.087
IS THIS THE GUY?HUH? OH, YEAH.

20:20.219 --> 20:21.436
THAT LOOKS LIKE HIM,
WHATEVER.

20:21.567 --> 20:23.352
- WAIT! BUT--
- TAKE HIM AWAY.

20:25.441 --> 20:28.878
OKAY, LET'S PUT AN END
TO THIS PATHETIC HOEDOWN.

20:29.009 --> 20:30.316
BRANNIGAN, READ THE THING.

20:30.445 --> 20:32.752
AND THE WINNER IS-- [ Drumroll ]

20:32.883 --> 20:34.319
IT FIGURES.

20:34.450 --> 20:36.365
WHO ELSE BUT ZAPP BRANNIGAN
WOULD BE JUDGING

20:36.496 --> 20:39.280
THE MOST CHAUVINISTIC,
DEGRADING, DEHUMANIZING--

20:39.412 --> 20:40.455
"LEELA"?

20:42.762 --> 20:44.460
WAIT, YOU'RE MAKING A--

20:44.590 --> 20:47.420
OH, LOOK AT THAT.

20:48.986 --> 20:50.901
I FEEL LIKE A PRINCESS!

20:51.031 --> 20:52.511
[ Sobbing ]

20:57.211 --> 20:59.258
WAIT, WHAT ARE YOU PEOPLE--
IDIOTS?

20:59.387 --> 21:03.435
I'M STILL GOING MANO A MANO
WITH THIS ENVELOPE.

21:03.566 --> 21:06.352
[ Grunting ]

21:06.481 --> 21:08.048
AND THE WINNER IS...

21:08.179 --> 21:10.442
MISS VEGA FOUR.

21:16.186 --> 21:18.145
[ Camera Shutters Clicking ]

21:19.756 --> 21:21.627
♪ THERE IT IS

21:21.758 --> 21:25.719
♪ MISS UNIVERSE

21:26.588 --> 21:29.243
♪ THERE IT IS

21:29.375 --> 21:33.769
♪ LOOKING WEIRD

21:33.901 --> 21:36.207
[ Sighing ]
I ALMOST HAD THAT TIARA.

21:36.337 --> 21:37.817
[ Sighing ]
ME, TOO.

21:37.948 --> 21:40.603
WELL, YOU GUYS MIGHT
BOTH BE LOSERS,
BUT I JUST MADE OUT

21:40.733 --> 21:43.388
WITH THAT RADIATOR WOMAN
FROM THE RADIATOR PLANET.

21:43.519 --> 21:45.955
FRY, THAT'S A RADIATOR.

21:46.086 --> 21:48.307
OH.
[ Clears Throat ]

21:48.436 --> 21:50.569
IS THERE A BURN WARD
WITHIN TEN FEET OF HERE?
